				 Signal of heavy showers
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT				 	 Caught in a shower on Monday evening. A Telegraph picture																								There will be widespread rain in the city on Tuesday, with heavy showers in some places, the Met office has warned.																								The low pressure that was hovering over north-east Bay of Bengal intensified and entered Bangladesh on Monday and was showing signs of moving north, according to the weatherman.																								Calcutta and the rest of Gangetic Bengal will receive fairly widespread rain under its influence, said G.C. Debnath, the director of the weather section at Regional Meteorological Centre in Alipore. 																								However, as the low pressure has entered land, there is no chance of it intensifying further, added Debnath.																								The city woke up to an overcast sky on Monday. There were spells of sharp showers in the afternoon and evening. On Sunday night, light to moderate rain had brought relief from the heat and humidity. 
